Films.DescriptionLong: Bank-teller Freud wakes up one day with a horse’s tail. Convinced that it’s connected to his dreams he meets an elderly oracle who prophesizes that he’s slowly becoming a horse. When he tells his Mathematics professor of how he dreamt of a horse with no tail, he’s told it represents a forgotten woman from his past. An astrologer interprets his dream as impotence. Piecing together the puzzle, Freud is visited by the woman from his dream. She is the spirit of the Rainbow, Van Ga, who helps him reach the parallel world of his childhood through a well. To the forgotten world of a little girl, with whom he’d promised to jump into the well, grow wings and fly away, like Neeli their Goddess. To this day, Neeli waits in the well. But Freud is now a 38-year-old man with a horse’s tail.
